  <text>
        <body>
            <div type="edition" xml:lang="grc">
                <ab>
                    <lb n="1"/>ἡ θεός
                   </ab>
            </div>
            <div type="apparatus"> 
                <app loc="1">
                <note>A variant reading suggests an adjective ᾔθεος with the subscript iota omitted.</note>
            </app>
            </div>
            <div type="translation">
                <p>[Dedicated to] female-deity.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The text reads ‘ΗΘΕΟC’ and can be interpreted as a dedication to an unknown female deity, represented by the noun θεός in nominative singular with the definite article ἡ. 
                    A variant reading suggests an adjective ᾔθεος, ‘unmarried youth’ with the subscript iota omitted. In this case the adjective would serve as an epithet or a simple acclamation.</p>
            </div>
